To program using galgebra sympy must be installed -

github.com/sympy/sympy

If you wish to put the modules in galgebra in the python path, open a terminal
in the galgebra subdirectory and run.

sudo python setgapth.py

for linux and 

python setgapth.py

for windows.

To use the LaTeX printing options in galgebra, a LaTeX distribution is required
containing pdflatex (texlive for linux, miktex for windows).

To use the enhanced printing options in windows ansicon must be installed -

github.com/adoxa/ansicon

It is strongly recommended that the geany editor/development environment be installed -

www.geany.org

for developing code using galgebra.



